  25:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****   ==============================================================================
  26:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                     ##### RAMCFG Peripheral features #####
  27:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****   ==============================================================================
  28:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****   [..]
  29:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     (+) Each SRAM is managed by a RAMCFG instance (AHBSRAM1/2, AXISRAM1 to 6,
  30:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****         BKPSRAM, FLEXRAM, and VENCRAM).
  31:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  32:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     (+) Each SRAM can be erased independently through its RAMCFG instance.
  33:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  34:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     (+) AXISRAM 1 to 6 are the main SRAMs. AHBSRAM1/2 are preferably for DMA-controlled
  35:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****         peripheral-to-memory data flow.
  36:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****         AXISRAM 2 to 6 can be shut down when the application is in Run mode.
  37:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  38:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     (+) FLEXMEM can be either allocated as Cortex-M55 TCM, or as system RAM
  39:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****         (FLEXRAM).
  40:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****         80 Kbytes of the FLEXMEM are retained in Standby mode, either allocated as
  41:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****         extended ITCM (64 +16-Kbyte ECC), or allocated as FLEXRAM.
  42:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  43:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     (+) The BKPSRAM content is retained in low-power modes, even when VDD is off
  44:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****         in VBAT mode. On a tamper event detection, the BKPSRAM content is erased.
  45:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  46:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     (+) The VENCRAM implements hardware and software erases.
  47:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  48:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     (+) FLEXRAM and BKPRAM support ECC correction feature:
  49:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****              (++) Single error detection and correction with interrupt generation.
  50:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****              (++) Double error detection with interrupt generation.
  51:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****              (++) Status with failing address
  52:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****   ==============================================================================
  53:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  54:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****   ==============================================================================
  55:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****   [..]
  56:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     (#) Call HAL_RAMCFG_Init() to initialize the RAMCFG peripheral before using
  57:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****        any feature. Call HAL_RAMCFG_DeInit() to de-initialize the RAMCFG when
  58:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****        using this peripheral is no more needed or a hardware issue has occurred.
  59:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****           (+) HAL_RAMCFG_Init() and HAL_RAMCFG_DeInit() APIs do not change the
  60:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               activation status of ECC feature. It is managed by
  61:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               HAL_RAMCFG_StartECC(), HAL_RAMCFG_StopECC() or option bytes (When
  62:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               available on the device).
  63:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  64:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****      *** ECC feature ***
  65:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****      ===================
  66:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     [..]
  67:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****           (+) Call HAL_RAMCFG_StartECC() and HAL_RAMCFG_StopECC() to enable and
  68:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               disable ECC hardware mechanism.
  69:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                     (++) When ECC feature is previously enabled (case of option
  70:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                          byte activation), calling HAL_RAMCFG_StartECC() is
  71:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                          recommended to enable the ECC address latching feature.
  72:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  73:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****           (+) Call HAL_RAMCFG_EnableNotification() and HAL_RAMCFG_DisableNotification()
  74:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               to enable and disable ECC interrupts. Interrupts can be:
  75:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                     (++) Single error interrupt.
  76:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                     (++) Double error interrupt.
  77:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                     (++) Double error interrupt redirected to Non maskable
  78:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****                           interrupt (NMI).
  79:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  80:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****           (+) Call HAL_RAMCFG_GetSingleErrorAddress() to get the address of the
  81:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               last fail RAM word detected (only for single error) and
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccHXHETX.s 			page 3


  82:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               call HAL_RAMCFG_GetDoubleErrorAddress() to get the address of the
  83:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               last fail RAM word detected (only for double error).
  84:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  85:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****           (+) Call HAL_RAMCFG_IsECCSingleErrorDetected() to check if an ECC single
  86:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               error was detected.
  87:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               Call HAL_RAMCFG_IsECCDoubleErrorDetected() to check if an ECC double
  88:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               error was detected.
  89:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               These APIs are used in silent mode (No ECC interrupt
  90:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               is enabled).
  91:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  92:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****      *** Erase feature ***
  93:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****      =====================
  94:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****     [..]
  95:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****           (+) Call HAL_RAMCFG_Erase() to launch a hardware erase for the given
  96:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               SRAM.
  97:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
  98:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****           (+) The erase value is equal to 0 when launching erase hardware through
  99:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               RAMCFG.
 100:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
 101:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****           (+) SRAM2 write protected pages are erased when performing an erase
 102:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c ****               through RAMCFG.
 103:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_ramcfg.c **** 
